posts.name: Benji Brunner
posts.cooked: Excellent robot as always it was a blast playing at MNDU with y’all! I love the deadbolt feature you guys added - do you have a video of it in action? Congrats on the win at state!

posts.name: Rocky
posts.cooked: Is this the bot that climbed the reef?

posts.name: Eli Bring
posts.cooked: The practice robot climbed the reef but same design

posts.name: Corey Applegate
posts.cooked: Technically the dead bolt locks the elevator after the climb. In the reef climb the motors held the robot at the top untill it let itself down and continued the match.

posts.name: Eli Bring
posts.cooked: The deadbolt was definitely an interesting add. We felt that the time sunk into a new climber or a ratchet inside the gearbox wasn’t worth it and we were too far into the elevator climb so we had to come up with something the deadbolt is still the original and hasn’t been swapped. Very durable and did the trick. Videos

posts.name: Nolan Evans
posts.cooked: I haven’t seen many robots using vex’s griplock wheels, cool robot

posts.name: Calvin Selin
posts.cooked: very important question:  could your bumpers be any taller?

posts.name: Adam
posts.cooked: I love how this robot is packaged, that climb is genius. Congratulations on going back to back at state!
